The paper deals with the training objective of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and proposes a novel algorithmic framework for GANs via an infinite-dimensional two-player game. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper also discusses the convergence rates and optimization procedures, which are relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a principled procedure to reduce the novel prox methods to simple sampling routines, which is related to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
